double-tense: No verb shows duplicated past morphology; 'saw' is a simple past form.
be-construction: There is no uninflected 'be' expressing habitual/generic aspect.
resultant-done: No aspectual 'done' occurs before a verb phrase.
come: There is no stance 'come' before a VP; 'come' is absent.
double-modal: No sequence of two modals occurs.
multiple-neg: There are no negative elements in the clause.
neg-inversion: No clause-initial negative auxiliary precedes the subject.
n-inv-neg-concord: There is no negative subject or negative verb; no negative concord.
zero-3sg-pres-s: The subject is 'we' (not 3sg) and the verb 'saw' is past, not present.
is-was-gen: No 'is' or 'was' with nonstandard agreement occurs.
zero-pl-s: The plural noun 'helicopters' carries plural -s; no zero plural marking.
double-object: No personal dative pattern (no subject‑coreferential object pronoun + NP); the verb is 'saw' + NP.
wh-qu1: There is no WH-question; no missing DO or copula in a WH-interrogative.
wh-qu2: No WH-clause is present, so no nonstandard inversion applies.
existential-it: No existential 'it' construction appears.
demonstrative-them: The word 'them' is not used.
appositive-pleonastic-pronoun: No NP is followed by a co-referential pronoun; the subject is just 'we'.
verb-stem: Past is marked by inflected 'saw'; there is no bare verb used as finite past.
past-tense-swap: 'Saw' is the standard past form; no participle or regularized past is used in place of SAE past.
zero-rel-pronoun: The modifier 'flying over head' is a nonfinite participial, not a finite subject relative missing 'who/that'.
preterite-had: There is no 'had' used to mark simple past.

sentence: We was trying to wave thems down, seem like they was getting the ones over on the rooftop, cause I did saw a few-  I could look down the street and see a few on- on- on the rooftop.
zero-poss: No possessive relationship is expressed without 's or a standard possessive; phrases like 'the ones over on the rooftop' are not possessive.
zero-copula: All contexts that would require BE have an overt form (e.g., 'We was...', 'they was...'); no clear subject–predicate slot lacks BE.
double-tense: There is no duplicated past morphology within a single verb word; 'did saw' is periphrastic, not reduplicated -ed on one verb.
be-construction: No uninflected habitual 'be' appears; only inflected 'was' occurs.
resultant-done: No preverbal 'done' marking completive aspect is present.
come: No stance/evaluative 'come' before a VP occurs.
double-modal: No sequence of two modals like 'might could' appears; only single modals such as 'could' occur.
multiple-neg: There are no multiple negative elements within a single clause (no 'ain't/never/nothing' combination).
neg-inversion: No clause begins with a negative auxiliary before the subject.
n-inv-neg-concord: There is no negative subject combined with a negative auxiliary (e.g., 'Nobody don’t...').
zero-3sg-pres-s: No clear 3sg present subject with a bare verb; 'seem like...' lacks an overt 3sg subject and is syntactically underspecified.
is-was-gen: Non-standard agreement with BE: 'We was trying...' and 'they was getting...' use 'was' with plural subjects.
zero-pl-s: No clearly plural NP lacks -s; 'the ones' has plural -s and 'a few—' trails off without a noun.
double-object: No personal dative frame like 'had us a...' with subject=object pronoun + NP occurs.
wh-qu1: There are no WH-questions with missing BE/DO; no WH-questions at all appear.
wh-qu2: No WH-question departs from SAE inversion patterns; no WH-questions are present.
existential-it: No existential 'it' introducing new entities appears.
demonstrative-them: 'them' does not occur as a determiner before a noun; 'thems' is an object-like pronoun in 'wave thems down'.
appositive-pleonastic-pronoun: No NP is followed by a co-referential pronoun in the same grammatical role within the clause.
verb-stem: No bare verb clearly serves as a finite past predicate; 'seem like' is formulaic/underspecified and other bare verbs are under a modal ('could look/see').
past-tense-swap: No non-SAE past/participle swap is used; 'did saw' is not a participle-as-past or irregularized past of the targeted type.
zero-rel-pronoun: No subject relative clause lacks an overt relative pronoun; 'the ones over on the rooftop' is a NP with a PP, not a relative clause.
preterite-had: No 'had' + verb is used for simple past.

sentence: And uh, I did saw someone climbing up    uh, uh I guess it was a sheet, to try to get off of  something, trying to get  uh, uh, up on the roof.
zero-poss: No noun–noun juxtaposition or nonstandard possessive pronoun is used; no possessive relation is expressed without SAE marking.
zero-copula: Where BE is required, it is overt ('I guess it was a sheet'); no copula/auxiliary BE deletion occurs.
double-tense: There is no duplicated past morphology within a single verb word; 'did saw' is cross-word and not a duplicated -ed form.
be-construction: No uninflected habitual 'be' appears; finite BE is 'was' in 'it was a sheet' with non-habitual meaning.
resultant-done: No aspectual 'done' occurs before a verb phrase.
come: The verb 'come' does not appear as a stance/evaluative marker.
double-modal: No sequence of two modals (e.g., might could) occurs.
multiple-neg: There are no multiple negative elements within a clause; negation is absent.
neg-inversion: No clause begins with a negative auxiliary before the subject.
n-inv-neg-concord: There is no negative subject plus negative auxiliary structure.
zero-3sg-pres-s: No 3sg present-tense verb lacks -s; the finite verb is past ('did').
is-was-gen: 'Was' agrees with the 3sg subject 'it' ('it was a sheet'); no generalized is/was usage.
zero-pl-s: No clearly plural noun appears without plural -s.
double-object: There is no personal dative frame with a coreferential object pronoun followed by an NP (e.g., 'got me a...').
wh-qu1: No WH-question is present; thus no zero copula/DO deletion in a WH-question.
wh-qu2: No WH-clause appears, so no nonstandard WH word order is present.
existential-it: 'It' in 'I guess it was a sheet' is referential, not existential introducing new entities.
demonstrative-them: The determiner 'them' does not appear before a noun.
appositive-pleonastic-pronoun: No NP is followed by a co‑referential pronoun in the same clause role.
bin: No 'BIN/been' appears without 'have' to mark remote past.
verb-stem: No bare verb stem serves as the finite predicate in a past context; 'did saw' contains a past-marked main verb.
past-tense-swap: Although 'did saw' is nonstandard, the feature targets participle/preterite distribution or regularized past forms (e.g., 'seen', 'knowed', 'had bit'), which are not present.
zero-rel-pronoun: No finite subject relative clause missing 'who/that' occurs; 'someone climbing...' is a nonfinite modifier.
preterite-had: There is no 'had' + past verb used for simple past meaning.
